# Domain Design Document

#### Purpose
This document defines the Domain Driven Design (DDD) architecture for an HSA-focused SaaS platform that enables users to:

Securely store medical receipts
Extract structured expense data via OCR
Track qualified medical expenses
Maintain a running reimbursable HSA balance
Preserve audit-ready records for future tax-free reimbursement
The MVP intentionally avoids:

Custody of funds
Investment advice
Direct tax filing
Money movement
The platform is positioned as:

A financial recordkeeping and reimbursement intelligence platform for HSA users.

#### Domain Vision

Core User Problem

**HSA users:**

Lose receipts
Forget reimbursable expenses
Fail to maximize tax advantages
Lack centralized lifetime tracking
Core Business Outcome

**Enable users to:**

Preserve qualified medical expenses indefinitely
Maintain audit-ready reimbursement records
Unlock delayed reimbursement strategies
Build tax-free liquidity over time

#### Ubiquitous Language

The following terms are standardized across engineering, product, support, and compliance.

**Term	Definition:**

Receipt	Uploaded proof of payment for medical expense
Expense	Structured medical transaction extracted from receipt
Qualified Expense	Expense believed to qualify under IRS Publication 502
Reimbursement Balance	Total unreimbursed qualified expenses
OCR Extraction	Parsed receipt data from uploaded image/PDF
Provider	Merchant, clinic, pharmacy, or healthcare vendor
Evidence Package	Immutable audit record associated with expense
User Vault	User’s long-term receipt storage space
Tag	Classification label assigned to expense
Verification Status	Confidence level of expense qualification
Account	Authenticated user identity
Audit Trail	Immutable record of system/user actions

